               <head>Hasan Shirazi’s History of Jahangir</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Muntakhab al-tavārīkh by Ḥasan ibn Muḥammadī Shīrāzī “Khākī”</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85148201 http://lccn.loc.gov/n84143316 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3734-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Compendium or mujmal of a world history and biography by Ḥasan Bayg, extending from creation to the hijrī year 1020
</p>
                        <p>Initially commissioned by the Timurid or Mughal Emperor Akbar I and completed under Emperor Jahāngīr, on 20 Rajab 1019
</p>
                        <p>Prefixed with a dībāchah by the Akbarī munshīʾ, Shaykh ʿAbd al-Laṭīf ibn ʿAbd Allāh ʿAbbāsī, describing circumstances of the author’s death in 1022
</p>
                        <p>Dated (f. 443r): 20 Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1145, year 15 of Muḥammad Shāh’s reign/3 May 1733</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 7 Sep. 1907
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21828">Muntakhab al-tavārīkh</title>
